body.head: NNA019478

p.note: See Publications of the Jesup North Pacific Expedition, Vol. X, pp. 195, 210, 222.

body.p:
"Don't go away!" said Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ to Only-One. "I shall go to see the child of Gwāʼᵋnālālis." Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ started. He saw Shaman-Woman. Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ was afraid of Shaman-Woman, and he went past inland from Shaman-Woman. Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ started, and he saw
something that was wrong. It was not a real man. It was not a real man, what was seen by Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ. He started, and he saw Łᴇxyāʼlik·aᵋlayū. He was afraid of him, and went past inland from Łᴇxyāʼlik·aᵋlayū. Q!āʼnēqīᵋlax̣ᵘ started. He was Greatest-Shaman at Having-Dead-Ones, the place of Greatest-Shaman. He passed inland from Greatest-Shaman.
